BT /F2 13.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 263.30 Tm (Agentic System Highlights) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 62.00 238.30 Tm (•) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 74.00 238.30 Tm (Hierarchical AAOSA: three real routing levels; every delegating agent negotiates) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 223.80 Tm (the inquiry via aaosa_instructions / aaosa_call.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 62.00 209.30 Tm (•) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 74.00 209.30 Tm (sly_data session memory: current client and identity are carried out-of-band and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 194.80 Tm (reused across turns - never re-typed into the prompt.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 62.00 180.30 Tm (•) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 74.00 180.30 Tm (Scoped-retrieval CodedTools: the retriever builds a path only from the requested) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 165.80 Tm (client and verifies it stays inside that client's folder - cross-client reads are) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 151.30 Tm (structurally impossible.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 62.00 136.80 Tm (•) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 74.00 136.80 Tm (Code-enforced access control: identity limits scope in Python, so the model cannot) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 122.30 Tm (be prompted into crossing a boundary.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 62.00 107.80 Tm (•) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 74.00 107.80 Tm (Grounding evaluation loop: every answer is checked against the source; if no rule) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 93.30 Tm (exists, the system escalates instead of inventing one.) Tj ET
